sentences: Bernette Epstein, known as Yara Bernette (March 14, 1920 – March 30, 2002), was a Brazilian classical pianist.

Considered one of Brazil's foremost pianists of the twentieth century, she achieved international renown for her performance of Classical and Romantic works, notably those of Rachmaninoff, Mozart, Chopin, Debussy, and Brazilian composer Heitor Villa-Lobos, in concerts in Brazil, Europe, and the United States.
